-- Sasfin Hires JSE’s Noah Greenhill to Head Corporate Finance Team
-- B y   S t e p h e n   G u n n i o n
-- 2012-02-05T10:47:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-05/sasfin-hires-jse-s-noah-greenhill-to-head-corporate-finance-team.html
Sasfin Holdings Ltd. (SFN)  appointed Noah Greenhill, a senior general manager at the Johannesburg Stock
Exchange, to head its corporate finance team, the Johannesburg-
based financial services group said.  Greenhill, who helped to set up the Johannesburg bourse’s
Alternative Exchange for small companies, will join Sasfin on
Feb. 13, replacing Panico Theocharides, who has resigned, the
lender said in a statement today.  Michelle Joubert, head of investor relations at  JSE Ltd. (JSE) ,
operator of the Johannesburg bourse, didn’t answer a call for
comment made to her cell phone.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Gunnion in Johannesburg at 
